WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:04.404
[cheerful music]

00:04.471 --> 00:12.379
♪ ♪

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
♪ Harvey ♪

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
♪ ♪

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
♪ Harvey ♪

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
♪ ♪

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
♪ Harvey ♪

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
♪ ♪

00:31.664 --> 00:35.802
[breathing heavily]

00:35.869 --> 00:38.004
Please leave me alone.

00:38.071 --> 00:40.673
You're fun to hang with.

00:40.740 --> 00:43.810
[upbeat music]

00:43.877 --> 00:45.812
[bells chime]

00:45.879 --> 00:49.516
Whoa.

00:49.582 --> 00:51.251
Yeah, whoo!

00:51.317 --> 00:53.787
Oh, yeah!

00:53.853 --> 00:56.856
[bicycle bell rings]

00:56.923 --> 00:58.057
Whoo.

00:58.124 --> 01:02.061
[bicycle bell rings]

01:02.128 --> 01:05.732
Here we go!

01:05.799 --> 01:07.867
I got lift!

01:07.934 --> 01:10.870
[upbeat music]

01:10.937 --> 01:13.873
♪ ♪

01:13.940 --> 01:15.975
{\an3}[breathing heavily]
Hey, Harvey.

01:16.042 --> 01:17.076
{\an1}Hey, Foo.

01:17.143 --> 01:18.545
What are we doing, running?

01:18.611 --> 01:23.216
We're riding bikes.
You want to join us?

01:23.283 --> 01:24.083
Yes!

01:24.150 --> 01:25.919
Uh, I don't know.

01:25.985 --> 01:27.987
I got enough cardio
for today.

01:28.054 --> 01:29.489
Yeah, I got to go too.

01:29.556 --> 01:32.525
{\an1}I got a date with, like,
50 ladies, you know.

01:32.592 --> 01:35.728
I got to go get ready.

01:35.795 --> 01:39.332
Oh, guess I'll just go play
with my stick.

01:39.399 --> 01:41.301
{\an1}No, man,
you're my best friend.

01:41.367 --> 01:43.770
{\an1}I'd love to ride bikes
with you.

01:43.837 --> 01:45.104
- Really?
- Sure.

01:45.171 --> 01:47.974
{\an1}So grab your bike,
and let's get our ride on!

01:48.041 --> 01:49.642
I don't have a bike.

01:49.709 --> 01:51.311
{\an3}So I'm just gonna have to hop
on the back of yours.

01:51.377 --> 01:53.513
{\an1}Oh, no!
What are you doing?

01:53.580 --> 01:56.182
I was getting ready
to ride a bike. Duh.

01:56.249 --> 01:59.519
Uh, I think we should
get you your own bike.

01:59.586 --> 02:03.523
{\an3}Harvey,
that would be amazing.

02:03.590 --> 02:06.526
[upbeat music]

02:06.593 --> 02:13.333
♪ ♪

02:13.399 --> 02:15.535
{\an9}Well, if we're gonna
get you a bike,

02:15.602 --> 02:17.036
{\an8}this is the place to go.

02:17.103 --> 02:18.171
[door bells jingle]

02:18.238 --> 02:20.106
{\an1}I want one with a bell
and a basket

02:20.173 --> 02:21.307
and three wheels and--

02:21.374 --> 02:22.876
{\an1}How many wheels does
a bike have again?

02:22.942 --> 02:24.344
- Usually two.
- Cool.

02:24.410 --> 02:26.579
{\an3}First we need to find
the shopkeep.

02:26.646 --> 02:28.615
Oh, hello.

02:28.681 --> 02:30.250
[bell rings]

02:30.316 --> 02:33.286
[sighs]
welcome to Randl's Rentls.

02:33.353 --> 02:35.188
Everything in here is mine.
I found it.

02:35.255 --> 02:36.956
It's mine. I rent it.
You don't own it.

02:37.023 --> 02:39.792
It's only out temporarily.
It's mine. What do you want?

02:39.859 --> 02:42.629
{\an1}I would like to rent a bike
for my good friend here.

02:42.695 --> 02:44.898
{\an1}And if it's possible,
we'd like--

02:44.964 --> 02:46.399
{\an3}Speed bike
with two wheels!

02:46.466 --> 02:49.235
Whoa there!
You want to rent my stuff,

02:49.302 --> 02:51.604
well, then you got to follow
my rules.

02:51.671 --> 02:54.641
Randl, you're gonna scare
these nice girls away.

02:54.707 --> 02:57.043
{\an1}Quiet, Ma!

02:57.110 --> 02:58.144
I'm sorry about her.

02:58.211 --> 03:00.013
She won't live in a home.

03:00.079 --> 03:01.614
I raised you wrong.

03:01.681 --> 03:04.450
{\an1}You're the one scaring away
the customers, Ma!

03:04.517 --> 03:06.753
{\an3}Uh, actually,
you wouldn't be interested

03:06.819 --> 03:09.289
{\an3}in renting a nice elderly lady,
would you?

03:09.355 --> 03:13.326
Wha--Uh, we'll just take
the bike, if that's okay.

03:13.393 --> 03:15.862
{\an1}Hey, d-don't touch
anything.

03:15.929 --> 03:18.565
{\an1}This is my favorite,
favorite bike.

03:18.631 --> 03:20.233
{\an1}20 bucks.

03:20.300 --> 03:23.636
{\an3}I've got 16 ones
and a silver dollar

03:23.703 --> 03:26.105
{\an3}my grandma gave to me
for my birthday.

03:26.172 --> 03:28.141
{\an3}This is all my money
in the world.

03:28.207 --> 03:30.043
Leave it on the floor.

03:30.109 --> 03:32.679
{\an3}Great. Come on, Foo,
we're leaving.

03:32.745 --> 03:36.082
Okay. Bye, lady.

03:36.149 --> 03:38.518
{\an1}It's perfect, Harvey.
It's perfect!

03:38.585 --> 03:40.353
Now we just have
to grab my bike,

03:40.420 --> 03:43.923
and we'll be all set.

03:43.990 --> 03:45.525
{\an1}Uh...

03:45.592 --> 03:47.794
{\an1}Are bikes
supposed to do that?

03:49.929 --> 03:51.698
Is there a problem?

03:51.764 --> 03:53.132
Hi. Yes, um...

03:53.199 --> 03:56.636
I think this bike
may be defective.

03:56.703 --> 03:58.771
{\an1}Well, you should have
rented the bolts

03:58.838 --> 04:01.674
that hold the bike together.

04:01.741 --> 04:02.775
[door bells jingle]

04:02.842 --> 04:04.143
Aw, corn bucket!

04:04.210 --> 04:07.180
{\an1}Well, I guess we won't ride
bikes together.

04:07.246 --> 04:08.581
No. You know what?

04:08.648 --> 04:10.883
{\an3}I'm not ready to
give up on this yet.

04:10.950 --> 04:12.485
One way or another, Foo,

04:12.552 --> 04:14.887
{\an3}today we are gonna
get you a bike.

04:14.954 --> 04:16.154
{\an1}But how?

04:16.221 --> 04:19.091
I don't know.
Let's ask Fee.

04:19.158 --> 04:20.426
Just steal it.

04:20.493 --> 04:22.128
We haven't even told you
our problem.

04:22.195 --> 04:23.730
Okay, shoot.

04:23.796 --> 04:26.199
Well, Randl won't give us
the bike, even though we--

04:26.265 --> 04:28.101
- Just steal it.
- Sounds like a plan.

04:28.167 --> 04:30.236
But we can't just
steal a bike.

04:30.303 --> 04:32.538
That's crazy.
Right?

04:32.605 --> 04:34.007
He's right.

04:34.073 --> 04:35.775
{\an1}If we're going back, we should
steal an even better one.

04:35.842 --> 04:38.611
Listen, dude, you already
paid for the bike, right?

04:38.678 --> 04:41.514
{\an3}It's only stealing
if you keep it.

04:41.581 --> 04:42.982
I guess that's true.

04:43.049 --> 04:45.818
Grandma did say not to waste
my birthday money.

04:45.885 --> 04:47.120
So what's the plan?

04:47.186 --> 04:49.255
I don't know,
but whatever it is,

04:49.322 --> 04:54.327
it's gonna be
really, really, really good.

04:54.394 --> 04:57.797
[door bells jingle]

04:57.864 --> 04:59.766
{\an1}Hello.
[clears throat]

04:59.832 --> 05:01.668
{\an1}[high-pitched voice]
Hello!

05:01.734 --> 05:05.371
{\an1}My husband and I are looking
for some fine jewelry.

05:05.438 --> 05:08.241
{\an1}You kids can't have
the bike back.

05:08.307 --> 05:12.812
{\an6}[high-pitched voice]
We are conducting a survey
on local businesses.

05:12.879 --> 05:15.748
{\an1}Wait. Which one of you
is supposed to be the wife?

05:15.815 --> 05:16.949
Is it you or you?

05:17.016 --> 05:19.052
{\an3}[normal voice]
Uh, he is.

05:19.118 --> 05:20.486
{\an3}Wait.

05:20.553 --> 05:23.890
{\an3}Harvey, it's me, Foo.
I forgot the plan again.

05:23.956 --> 05:26.926
{\an4}[normal voice]
Just sneak off and go find
the bikes in the back.

05:26.993 --> 05:28.494
I'll stall him.

05:28.561 --> 05:31.097
{\an3}Be sure to get the one
with the bolts this time.

05:31.164 --> 05:32.699
Right.

05:32.765 --> 05:34.367
{\an3}[high-pitched voice]
Heh heh. So...

05:34.434 --> 05:36.035
[metal clangs]

05:36.102 --> 05:37.770
Do you come here often?

05:37.837 --> 05:39.305
This is my store.

05:39.372 --> 05:40.606
{\an3}Oh, right.

05:40.673 --> 05:41.774
[metal crashes]

05:41.841 --> 05:46.412
{\an3}Uh, I have to go use
the little, uh...

05:46.479 --> 05:48.748
woman's room?

05:48.815 --> 05:51.751
You know I can see you
walking over to the bikes.

05:51.818 --> 05:54.020
And now you're taking one
off the rack.

05:54.087 --> 05:56.689
Now you're heading towards
the fire exit.

05:56.756 --> 05:58.157
[door bells jingle,
alarm blares]

05:58.224 --> 05:59.792
{\an1}And now you're leaving
the store.

05:59.859 --> 06:02.428
{\an6}[normal voice]
Wow. These disguises
really worked.

06:02.495 --> 06:04.163
I love being a girl.

06:04.230 --> 06:06.399
{\an3}No, Foo.
I'm the girl, remember?

06:06.466 --> 06:08.601
{\an1}Hey, I can see you
out there!

06:08.668 --> 06:11.170
You've got five seconds
to bring that bike back,

06:11.237 --> 06:13.005
or I'll come get it myself.

06:13.072 --> 06:14.207
And you don't want that.

06:14.273 --> 06:15.842
Foo, get on the bike.

06:15.908 --> 06:17.777
{\an3}I'll hop on the pegs
and we'll head to my house.

06:17.844 --> 06:20.379
{\an1}But I don't know how
to ride a bike. You drive it.

06:20.446 --> 06:22.415
{\an3}I can't.
I don't have my helmet.

06:22.482 --> 06:23.716
I never ride without it.

06:23.783 --> 06:26.219
{\an1}Then we'll ride
to your house and get it.

06:26.285 --> 06:28.387
Do you not get
how this works?

06:28.454 --> 06:30.456
I see you guys arguing.

06:30.523 --> 06:32.191
I'm coming over.

06:32.258 --> 06:33.226
[both gasp]

06:33.292 --> 06:36.796
Come on! Let's go!

06:36.863 --> 06:39.031
{\an1}I'll just have to teach you
how to ride a bike.

06:39.098 --> 06:41.501
{\an3}Okay!

06:43.536 --> 06:47.273
Let's hide here.

06:48.274 --> 06:49.909
{\an1}I think
we're in the clear.

06:49.976 --> 06:51.010
Let's try again.

06:51.077 --> 06:53.212
Hands go here.
Feet go here.

06:53.279 --> 06:56.449
And one last thing.

06:56.516 --> 06:59.152
{\an1}Now, concentrate and find
your center of gravity.

06:59.218 --> 07:01.921
I feel alive inside.

07:01.988 --> 07:03.055
[bicycle bell rings]

07:03.122 --> 07:05.391
{\an3}[grunting]
Am I moving?

07:05.458 --> 07:07.493
{\an1}[laughs]
Kind of. No worries.

07:07.560 --> 07:08.361
{\an3}Huh?

07:08.427 --> 07:09.762
[both scream]

07:09.829 --> 07:12.131
Okay, Foo, try it again,
just like I showed you.

07:12.198 --> 07:13.499
I can't do it, Harvey!

07:13.566 --> 07:15.601
{\an3}Yes, you can, man.
You've got this.

07:15.668 --> 07:17.637
We're dead, Harvey.
We're dead!

07:17.703 --> 07:21.040
Hold up. Time to back off,
you cheapskate nut job.

07:21.107 --> 07:24.310
{\an3}Go and ride bikes, dudes.
I'll take care of this guy.

07:24.377 --> 07:26.512
Thanks, Fee.

07:26.579 --> 07:29.448
{\an3}Okay, you raccooned piece
of dump,

07:29.515 --> 07:31.951
do your worst.

07:33.953 --> 07:35.354
[crash]

07:35.421 --> 07:37.356
{\an1}(Fee)
I slowed him down for you.

07:37.423 --> 07:38.658
Go, go, go, go, go!

07:38.724 --> 07:40.293
Get on your bike!
Hop on your bike!

07:40.359 --> 07:42.528
{\an1}Hop on your bike!
Get up! Get up! Get up!

07:42.595 --> 07:46.032
Go, go, go, go, go!

07:46.098 --> 07:48.401
[sniffing]

07:48.467 --> 07:49.602
They're close.

07:49.669 --> 07:51.437
You two better give it up.

07:51.504 --> 07:54.607
I'm not afraid to throw
a pair of kids in jail.

07:54.674 --> 07:57.176
You wouldn't be
the first ones.

07:57.243 --> 07:58.444
That was close.

07:58.511 --> 08:01.047
{\an1}We got to figure out a way
to outrun Randl--

08:01.113 --> 08:04.550
maybe something
involving glue?

08:04.617 --> 08:05.585
{\an1}Huh.

08:05.651 --> 08:06.886
{\an3}(Foo)
Harvey, listen...

08:06.953 --> 08:08.688
{\an3}I don't want you
to go to jail.

08:08.754 --> 08:11.090
{\an3}I'm the one that
got you into this.

08:11.157 --> 08:12.692
You've done so much for me.

08:12.758 --> 08:15.061
{\an3}You even dressed up like
a really pretty girl.

08:15.127 --> 08:17.029
You were so pretty, Harvey.

08:17.096 --> 08:19.265
{\an3}You're a really
very good friend.

08:19.332 --> 08:22.902
{\an3}But maybe I'm just more of
a stick kind of guy, you know?

08:22.969 --> 08:27.006
{\an3}Riding bikes sounds really,
really, really cool,

08:27.073 --> 08:30.509
{\an3}but not if it means
getting you in trouble.

08:30.576 --> 08:33.546
{\an1}(Harvey)
Foo, that's it.

08:33.613 --> 08:34.847
{\an1}I think I figured out
a way

08:34.914 --> 08:36.816
{\an1}we can get your bike ride
after all.

08:36.883 --> 08:39.150
{\an1}We just have to get
to the top of that hill.

08:39.217 --> 08:42.520
{\an1}Once we do that, it'll be
all downhill from--

08:42.587 --> 08:44.323
Give me back my bike.

08:44.390 --> 08:46.459
[both scream]

08:46.525 --> 08:49.462
[breathing heavily]

08:49.528 --> 08:52.265
Oh, my tassels!

08:52.331 --> 08:55.268
[upbeat music]

08:55.334 --> 08:59.538
♪ ♪

08:59.605 --> 09:02.108
[breathing heavily]

09:02.174 --> 09:05.678
[both breathing heavily]

09:05.745 --> 09:08.014
My bike!

09:08.080 --> 09:11.550
Foo, we're gonna make it.

09:11.617 --> 09:13.686
- Yay.
- Yay.

09:13.753 --> 09:16.255
{\an1}Oh. Oh.

09:16.322 --> 09:17.356
Ready, Foo?

09:17.423 --> 09:19.058
{\an3}So ready.

09:19.125 --> 09:23.429
[imitates motor revving]

09:23.496 --> 09:26.666
I believe in you, dude.

09:26.732 --> 09:28.100
[gasps]

09:28.167 --> 09:30.336
{\an1}Bike!

09:30.403 --> 09:31.637
[both scream]

09:31.704 --> 09:33.172
Get off! Get off!
Get off! Get off!

09:33.239 --> 09:35.107
{\an3}Aah! Oh.

09:35.174 --> 09:37.176
{\an3}Here's your bolt back,
Mister.

09:37.243 --> 09:39.178
{\an3}Yay!

09:39.245 --> 09:41.280
Go, Foo, go!

09:41.347 --> 09:45.384
[slow, triumphant music]

09:45.451 --> 09:50.656
{\an1}[slowed]
Foo, you're riding.

09:50.723 --> 09:56.295
{\an3}[slowed]
No, we're riding.

09:56.362 --> 09:59.932
[slowed laughter]

09:59.999 --> 10:03.069
{\an3}Whoa.

10:03.135 --> 10:06.105
[both grunting]

10:06.172 --> 10:07.106
Ooh!

10:07.173 --> 10:08.107
Oh!

10:08.174 --> 10:09.675
- Oh!
- Aah!

10:09.742 --> 10:12.745
- Aah!
- Oh!

10:14.747 --> 10:17.850
[bicycle bells ring]

10:17.917 --> 10:20.886
{\an1}We did it.

10:20.953 --> 10:23.723
Oh, you two look really hurt.

10:23.789 --> 10:25.958
But I still need
my bike back.

10:26.025 --> 10:28.094
{\an9}[coughs]
Ow!

10:28.160 --> 10:29.595
{\an9}You know what?
Take it!

10:29.662 --> 10:32.264
{\an9}I promised my friend
we'd ride together today

10:32.331 --> 10:33.566
{\an9}and, uh--

10:33.632 --> 10:37.937
{\an9}Whoa.
I stood up too fast.

10:38.004 --> 10:40.973
{\an3}We regret nothing!
Right, Foo?

10:41.040 --> 10:41.974
{\an3}Foo?

10:42.041 --> 10:43.242
{\an3}Uh-oh.

10:43.309 --> 10:46.879
That was the best ride
I've ever had!

10:48.280 --> 10:50.683
Thanks, Harvey.

10:50.750 --> 10:53.853
{\an3}Hey, Mister, you can take
the bikes back now.

10:53.919 --> 10:57.223
All right. Pleasure
doing business with you.

11:00.059 --> 11:03.295
Hey, wait.
One of those is mi--

11:03.362 --> 11:05.531
Oh, well.

11:05.598 --> 11:09.035
{\an3}Come on, I know some even more
bigger hills back that way.

11:09.101 --> 11:12.872
{\an3}Okay, first we got to find
our center of gravity.

11:12.938 --> 11:15.174
- Harvey?
- Coming!

11:17.109 --> 11:20.046
[upbeat music]

11:20.112 --> 11:22.381
♪ ♪

11:22.448 --> 11:25.251
{\an1}[claps]

11:27.353 --> 11:29.822
{\an3}Hey, Piri Piri,
I have something for you.

11:29.889 --> 11:31.490
Happy Valentine's Day!

11:31.557 --> 11:33.125
Oh, my gosh!

11:33.192 --> 11:35.194
{\an1}Claire, that is the best
Valentine's card I've ever seen.

11:35.261 --> 11:37.797
{\an3}Really? My mom said
I cut it crooked.

11:37.863 --> 11:39.932
No! It's perfect.

11:39.999 --> 11:42.101
{\an1}I got something
for you too.

11:42.168 --> 11:44.036
Ta-da!

11:44.103 --> 11:45.805
Oh, um, wow.

11:45.871 --> 11:47.773
That's very thoughtful.

11:47.840 --> 11:49.775
{\an1}Here, I really want you
to embrace it.

11:49.842 --> 11:51.043
Oh.
[chuckles awkwardly]

11:51.110 --> 11:53.546
{\an3}Gosh, I love
Valentine's Day.

11:53.612 --> 11:55.548
Do you guys like
my Cupid wings?

11:55.614 --> 11:57.283
{\an3}My mom helped me
make 'em.

11:57.349 --> 11:59.385
Your mom rules.

11:59.452 --> 12:02.054
{\an3}You guys ready to get
some love and cards

12:02.121 --> 12:04.557
{\an3}and candy and love
and sweetness and hugs?

12:04.623 --> 12:06.325
Knock on the stinkin' door
already.

12:06.392 --> 12:08.294
I want candy.

12:08.360 --> 12:11.030
{\an3}Oh, hey, Harvey.
Happy Valentine's Day.

12:11.097 --> 12:12.164
Hey, Mikey.

12:12.231 --> 12:13.332
(both)
Happy Valentine's Day!

12:13.399 --> 12:14.467
Aah!

12:14.533 --> 12:16.302
{\an1}I come bearing
a Valentine's gift

12:16.368 --> 12:18.003
from me to you.

12:18.070 --> 12:20.406
Wow.
Thanks, Harvey.

12:20.473 --> 12:21.574
This is awesome.

12:21.640 --> 12:23.476
{\an1}I inhaled
a lot of glitter,

12:23.542 --> 12:25.010
but it was worth it.

12:25.077 --> 12:26.345
{\an1}[coughs]

12:26.412 --> 12:27.847
{\an3}Here, I made this
for you.

12:27.913 --> 12:29.648
Look, I made you one too.

12:29.715 --> 12:31.584
{\an3}Oh, okay.

12:31.650 --> 12:33.853
Yeah, I made it
with real bugs.

12:33.919 --> 12:35.387
Happy Valentine's.

12:35.454 --> 12:37.189
{\an1}I made this for you.
Blech!

12:37.256 --> 12:41.260
{\an1}This piece is
the best-tasting one for you.

12:41.327 --> 12:44.430
{\an3}Um, thanks?

12:46.699 --> 12:48.501
All right, see ya.

12:48.567 --> 12:50.703
Hey, don't worry, guys.

12:50.769 --> 12:54.540
He's probably getting your
Valentine's goodies right now.

12:54.607 --> 12:56.208
Oh, hey, Harvey.
What's up?

12:56.275 --> 13:00.279
Oh, yeah. You forgot to give
Fee and Foo their Valentines.

13:00.346 --> 13:01.914
Oh, right. Yeah.

13:01.981 --> 13:04.316
{\an5}[whispering]
I don't have cards
or anything for them

13:04.383 --> 13:07.987
because I don't--
I don't really like them.

13:08.053 --> 13:09.188
So...

13:09.255 --> 13:13.058
anyway, bye.

13:13.125 --> 13:14.326
Wha--

13:14.393 --> 13:15.728
Oh.

13:15.794 --> 13:17.163
Oh, that's okay.

13:17.229 --> 13:20.332
{\an1}I guess this day isn't
really for us after all.

13:22.701 --> 13:25.538
I hate Valentine's Day.

13:25.604 --> 13:28.541
[quirky music]

13:28.607 --> 13:35.581
♪ ♪

13:35.648 --> 13:37.183
Hang in there, guys.

13:37.249 --> 13:39.451
{\an3}I know the next house is gonna
have a bunch of Valentines

13:39.518 --> 13:40.686
for you too.

13:40.753 --> 13:43.589
{\an3}I can feel it in my little
Cupid wings.

13:43.656 --> 13:45.357
That's easy for you to say.

13:45.424 --> 13:47.126
You already have so many.

13:47.193 --> 13:49.962
Foo and me still have
sacks full of nothing.

13:50.029 --> 13:52.164
{\an1}Yep, mine's still
pretty empty,

13:52.231 --> 13:53.933
except I found
this old shoe,

13:53.999 --> 13:55.501
{\an1}but I think
I put it there.

13:55.568 --> 13:58.270
{\an3}But, guys, Valentine's
is so cool.

13:58.337 --> 14:01.073
{\an3}It's about love
and being nice to each other

14:01.140 --> 14:03.042
{\an3}and kissing,
if you're old enough.

14:03.108 --> 14:04.877
Valentine's
isn't about love.

14:04.944 --> 14:06.145
It's about stuff.

14:06.212 --> 14:09.014
Everyone wants cute cards
and candy,

14:09.081 --> 14:11.083
but somebody
always gets left out.

14:11.150 --> 14:14.620
Will you be my Valentine?

14:14.687 --> 14:15.754
[groans]

14:15.821 --> 14:18.324
The whole Valentine's Day thing

14:18.390 --> 14:19.658
is rotten.

14:19.725 --> 14:22.595
We need a new day,
a darker day.

14:22.661 --> 14:23.696
You mean like night?

14:23.762 --> 14:26.732
No, an Anti-Valentine's Day.

14:26.799 --> 14:30.069
{\an3}A w-w-what?

14:30.135 --> 14:32.171
{\an1}Everyone just likes
to get cards.

14:32.238 --> 14:33.839
They don't care
what they say.

14:33.906 --> 14:36.842
{\an3}Whoa, I can feel
what you're writing.

14:36.909 --> 14:39.345
{\an1}Are you really gonna give that
to someone?

14:39.411 --> 14:42.348
{\an3}Um, yeah.

14:42.414 --> 14:44.817
Happy Anti-Valentine's Day,
Mikey.

14:44.883 --> 14:47.152
I made you something.

14:47.219 --> 14:49.888
{\an3}You--you think
I smell like farts?

14:49.955 --> 14:52.558
Yes. Now, you make
a card for me.

14:52.625 --> 14:55.628
{\an3}Um, okay.

14:55.694 --> 14:57.196
{\an3}[snickers]

14:57.263 --> 14:58.063
Here you go.

14:58.130 --> 15:00.699
"You are a butt."

15:00.766 --> 15:02.501
Look, Foo,
we got a card!

15:02.568 --> 15:03.702
{\an1}We did?

15:03.769 --> 15:05.604
Yeah.
It says we're butts.

15:05.671 --> 15:06.939
{\an1}We are?

15:07.006 --> 15:08.374
- Thanks, Mikey!
- Yeah, thanks, Mikey.

15:08.440 --> 15:10.342
{\an3}Sure.
Happy Anti-Valentine's Day.

15:10.409 --> 15:13.512
{\an5}(Foo)
My first real card.
Anti-Valentine's Day rules!

15:13.579 --> 15:14.913
{\an3}(Fee)
Yeah!

15:14.980 --> 15:17.816
Hey, guys, wait for me!

15:19.018 --> 15:20.185
[grumbling]

15:20.252 --> 15:22.121
I wonder if I have any--
Oh!

15:22.187 --> 15:24.156
Oh, my gosh, a Valentine's.

15:24.223 --> 15:26.692
Ha ha!
Harvey, was this you, man?

15:26.759 --> 15:28.327
Oh, Harvey, you sneak.

15:31.330 --> 15:32.398
What?

15:32.464 --> 15:34.166
Is this some kind
of sick joke?

15:34.233 --> 15:38.604
This card claims
that I "smell like old feet,"

15:38.671 --> 15:39.938
which is insane.

15:40.005 --> 15:42.308
{\an1}People stop me on the street
just to tell me

15:42.374 --> 15:43.776
I smell like mint

15:43.842 --> 15:45.144
because I brush
my teeth daily.

15:45.210 --> 15:47.713
{\an1}So this entire thing is
completely false!

15:47.780 --> 15:49.581
{\an3}Dade, we all got cards
like that.

15:49.648 --> 15:51.183
It's supposed to be funny.

15:51.250 --> 15:53.118
{\an1}Who is responsible
for this?

15:53.185 --> 15:56.121
(Fee)
We are.

15:58.991 --> 16:00.993
Happy Anti-Valentine's Day!

16:01.060 --> 16:03.162
{\an1}There's nothing happy
about this note.

16:03.228 --> 16:04.496
{\an1}I don't smell weird
at all.

16:04.563 --> 16:06.598
{\an1}Harvey's my witness,
and he totally agrees.

16:06.665 --> 16:10.035
{\an3}Actually, Dade,
you kind of smell like,

16:10.102 --> 16:11.603
I want to say hot dogs.

16:11.670 --> 16:13.739
Kids of Little Bark Grove,

16:13.806 --> 16:15.674
I come with a message.

16:15.741 --> 16:17.276
Valentine's Day bites!

16:17.343 --> 16:18.711
Aah!

16:18.777 --> 16:21.380
Who wants a sappy card
that don't mean squat?

16:21.447 --> 16:22.715
No, not me.

16:22.781 --> 16:25.017
{\an3}Why don't we give
each other fun cards?

16:25.084 --> 16:26.552
I like fun cards.

16:26.618 --> 16:28.520
Yeah, farts are fun!

16:28.587 --> 16:30.656
Telling people what's
wrong with them is fun.

16:30.723 --> 16:31.690
Boo-yah!

16:31.757 --> 16:33.759
[laughs and snorts]

16:33.826 --> 16:35.294
Oh, I just snorted.

16:35.361 --> 16:37.896
I can't read,
but I'll cherish this.

16:37.963 --> 16:39.565
Who's with me?

16:39.631 --> 16:41.066
I don't know.

16:41.133 --> 16:42.935
Harvey, you're the king
of Valentine's Day.

16:43.001 --> 16:44.236
What do you think?

16:44.303 --> 16:46.772
{\an1}Yeah, Harvey, you tell 'em
what you think.

16:46.839 --> 16:49.842
Uh, well...

16:49.908 --> 16:51.510
Yeah, I like it.

16:51.577 --> 16:55.381
{\an3}Long live
Anti-Valentine's Day!

16:55.447 --> 16:57.116
[laughs evilly]

16:57.182 --> 16:58.917
[cheers and applause]

16:58.984 --> 17:00.185
[all coughing]

17:00.252 --> 17:02.087
{\an1}Aah!
It's in my eyes!

17:03.856 --> 17:06.157
{\an5}(girl)
"Your head looks like a butt
with a wig on it!"

17:06.224 --> 17:07.726
(boy)
"This is you."

17:07.792 --> 17:08.727
(boy)
"No."

17:08.794 --> 17:11.930
[laughter]

17:15.300 --> 17:16.935
Oh, hey, there, Francois.

17:17.002 --> 17:18.237
I have a card for you.

17:18.303 --> 17:21.339
{\an3}Uh, wait, no.
Maybe this is too mean.

17:21.406 --> 17:23.175
{\an3}Okay, um...

17:23.242 --> 17:26.310
happy Anti-Valentine's Day.

17:26.377 --> 17:28.547
{\an1}You having fun
over there, Foo?

17:28.614 --> 17:30.449
I have so many cards

17:30.516 --> 17:32.084
{\an1}that I built an igloo
out of 'em.

17:32.151 --> 17:35.621
{\an1}I can fit my whole body
in here.

17:38.290 --> 17:40.559
{\an1}Hey, you okay there,
buddy?

17:40.626 --> 17:42.094
Yeah, I'm okay.

17:42.161 --> 17:44.396
{\an3}It's just everyone
stopped giving me cards.

17:44.463 --> 17:46.865
{\an3}I think I'm writing mine wrong
or something.

17:46.932 --> 17:48.700
Let me see.

17:48.767 --> 17:51.537
{\an1}"Sometimes you seem grouchy,
but you mean well,

17:51.603 --> 17:54.106
{\an1}"and you're probably
just tired.

17:54.173 --> 17:56.308
{\an1}"So I hope you get
more rest soon

17:56.375 --> 17:58.310
{\an1}because you deserve it.
Love, Harvey."

17:58.377 --> 18:00.312
{\an1}Harvey, this is
way too nice.

18:00.379 --> 18:02.014
{\an1}No wonder no one is
giving you cards.

18:02.080 --> 18:04.817
{\an1}You have to write
something dumb or rude.

18:04.883 --> 18:06.852
{\an3}Um, okay.

18:06.919 --> 18:08.554
So something like this?

18:08.620 --> 18:10.222
Harvey, come on.

18:10.289 --> 18:12.958
{\an1}Just write the rudest thing
you can think of.

18:13.025 --> 18:14.560
- Toenails.
- Ruder.

18:14.626 --> 18:15.594
Two toenails.

18:15.661 --> 18:17.129
No, not toenails!

18:17.196 --> 18:19.798
I want you to look
in the deepest,

18:19.865 --> 18:22.334
darkest part
of your soul.

18:22.401 --> 18:26.004
{\an3}Okay, but it's not
a pretty place.

18:26.071 --> 18:29.341
{\an3}[groaning]

18:35.013 --> 18:36.882
Whoa! Whoa.

18:36.949 --> 18:39.318
Foo, look what
Harvey wrote.

18:39.384 --> 18:42.221
{\an1}[mumbling]

18:42.287 --> 18:44.690
{\an1}I thought
I knew you, Harvey.

18:44.756 --> 18:48.694
I know, right? Now, go give this
to somebody special.

18:53.899 --> 18:54.933
{\an3}Uh, uh...

18:55.000 --> 18:56.368
{\an3}(Irving)
Hey, Hon.

18:56.435 --> 18:57.970
Do you know where
the scissors are?

18:58.036 --> 19:02.140
{\an3}I was making you a Valentine,
and it got glued to my...

19:02.207 --> 19:04.643
{\an3}Oh, my gosh! Why would you
say that to your mother?

19:04.710 --> 19:05.911
Don't look, egg.

19:05.978 --> 19:07.312
{\an3}You go to your room,
young man!

19:07.379 --> 19:09.014
You are grounded!

19:09.081 --> 19:11.617
But, Mom, it's funny
because it's slightly true.

19:11.683 --> 19:13.886
It's all in the spirit
of the holiday!

19:13.952 --> 19:16.488
No! No! Please wait!

19:16.555 --> 19:19.491
[somber music]

19:19.558 --> 19:21.159
♪ ♪

19:21.226 --> 19:23.095
[leaves rustling]

19:23.161 --> 19:25.297
{\an3}Oh!
[laughs] Ow.

19:25.364 --> 19:27.165
{\an3}Hey, Harvey.
I've been looking for ya.

19:27.232 --> 19:28.734
{\an3}How come you're
in your room?

19:28.800 --> 19:31.737
{\an1}Mom didn't like the rude card,
so Dad grounded me.

19:31.803 --> 19:33.205
Are you an idiot?

19:33.272 --> 19:34.573
{\an3}You weren't supposed
to give it to your mom.

19:34.640 --> 19:37.409
{\an1}You told me to give it
to someone special.

19:37.476 --> 19:38.710
{\an1}[groans]

19:38.777 --> 19:40.913
{\an1}Maybe this holiday isn't
for people like me.

19:40.979 --> 19:44.249
{\an3}Harvey, I didn't mean
for any of this to happen.

19:44.316 --> 19:47.019
{\an3}It just felt nice not
being left out for once.

19:47.085 --> 19:49.688
I know, but I--

19:49.755 --> 19:52.691
I just want to be alone.

20:00.599 --> 20:03.135
Come with us.

20:03.201 --> 20:06.138
[gulps]

20:06.204 --> 20:09.141
[ominous music]

20:09.207 --> 20:17.349
♪ ♪

20:20.352 --> 20:21.954
We're here.

20:22.020 --> 20:23.855
This is where rude kids go.

20:23.922 --> 20:25.090
What?

20:25.157 --> 20:26.191
[grunts]

20:26.258 --> 20:27.793
No! I'm sorry!

20:27.859 --> 20:29.628
I don't want
to go down the hole!

20:29.695 --> 20:32.264
There's so many things
I haven't gotten to do yet!

20:32.331 --> 20:36.835
I haven't had pizza
with pineapple!

20:36.902 --> 20:39.237
[insects chirping]

20:39.304 --> 20:42.174
Okay, go on, do it.

20:42.240 --> 20:44.476
I deserve it.

20:44.543 --> 20:45.911
Huh?

20:45.978 --> 20:48.914
"I'm a lumpy butt face."

20:48.981 --> 20:50.682
You sure are.

20:50.749 --> 20:52.150
I don't get it.

20:52.217 --> 20:54.286
You're gonna insult me
then throw me in the hole?

20:54.353 --> 20:55.654
{\an3}No, Harvey.

20:55.721 --> 20:57.923
{\an3}We were thinking something
more like this.

20:57.990 --> 20:59.224
{\an3}[whistles]

20:59.291 --> 21:01.760
(all)
Happy Anti-Valentine's Day!

21:01.827 --> 21:04.029
[cheering]

21:04.096 --> 21:05.597
What's up, Lumpy Butt?

21:05.664 --> 21:07.866
{\an3}Look,
I'm a zombie Cupid.

21:07.933 --> 21:09.368
Wait, what? Huh?

21:09.434 --> 21:14.072
{\an1}It's a party, dummy.
Look!

21:14.139 --> 21:16.642
(Harvey)
I still don't understand.

21:16.708 --> 21:20.078
{\an3}Fee explained the whole
"new holiday" thing to us,

21:20.145 --> 21:22.180
{\an3}and then we felt bad
for grounding you.

21:22.247 --> 21:25.283
So we're having
a party instead!

21:25.350 --> 21:27.486
{\an1}We get it. It's fun
to be rude sometimes.

21:27.552 --> 21:30.389
{\an1}Just please don't ever write
anything like that again.

21:30.455 --> 21:32.924
It was disturbing.

21:32.991 --> 21:34.326
Oh.
[chuckles] Okay.

21:34.393 --> 21:37.696
[laughter]

21:37.763 --> 21:39.131
Ow.

21:39.197 --> 21:40.532
Hold on.

21:40.599 --> 21:43.168
A box full of broccoli
and office supplies?

21:43.235 --> 21:45.270
What? You guys.

21:45.337 --> 21:46.772
[cheering]

21:46.838 --> 21:49.975
You know what?
This holiday is pretty swell.

21:50.042 --> 21:52.944
I love everyone so much.

21:53.011 --> 21:57.549
{\an1}Man, Harvey,
you just don't get it at all.
